                    " \nWORKING ON FIRE (WOF)\n ",
                    " \n \nRECEPTIONIST / ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT\nDuration: Fixed Term Contract of Employment until 05 January 2028\nLocation: Johannesburg, Sandton\n \nJob Profile:\nThe Receptionist / Administrative Assistant plays a crucial role in maintaining the smooth functioning of the office. The position involves a combination of administrative, secretarial, and front desk responsibilities. You will provide essential support to managers, employees, and visitors.\n\nReports to: Personal Assistant of Managing Director\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nAssisting with all aspects of office administrative tasks\nAnswer telephones and give information to callers, take messages or transfer calls to appropriate personnel in the office\nCoordinating between departments and operating units in resolving day-to-day administrative and operational issues\nScheduling and coordinating meetings, boardroom usage, interviews, events and other similar activities\nSending out and receiving mail and packages\nPreparing business correspondence (using word processing, spreadsheet, and presentation computer software)\nManaging documentation, correspondence and filing in the MD\u2019s office\nOrdering and receiving supplier deliveries\nPerforming multifaceted general office support\nPreparing meeting minutes and notes when required\nPreparing meeting packs when required\nArrange conference, meeting or travel reservations for staff members when\n \nRequired minimum qualification and work experience:\nMatric (Grade 12) qualification\nA minimum of 5 years Office Administration experience\nMust be in possession of a valid driver\u2019s licence\nComputer literate\n \nSkills:\nMaintains integrity, particularly in dealing with confidential information\nObserving the best business practice and etiquette\nGood organising capabilities\nGood communication skills\nStrong work ethic\nProductivity\nProfessionalism\nProblem-solving and critical thinking skills\nTechnical skills\nInterpersonal skills\nCommunication skills\nCustomer focus\nTeamwork and collaboration skills",
                    "Closing date: Tuesday, 02 July 2024\n \nSubmit CV together with a motivational letter to: talentad2024@wofire.co.za\n \nNOTE: Clearly indicate in the subject line the position for which you are applying.\n \nIf you have not had a response from us within 30 days after the closing date, kindly accept that your application has been unsuccessful. In line with the EEA, preference will be given to those applicants whose appointment will address the demographic imbalances in our work force profile."
