                    " \nWATER RESEARCH COMMISSION (WRC)\n ",
                    " \n \nHEAD: LEGAL AND AUXILIARY SERVICES - PERMANENT\nHead: Legal and Auxiliary Services in the Corporate Services Branch\n\n \nThis position calls for a team player with excellent management, planning and execution skills and the ability to build efficiencies and effectiveness to deliver on the strategy. The incumbent will be responsible for providing strategic direction by providing legal counsel and support on the organization , this includes diverse areas such as contracts, litigation, dispute resolution and labour issues. This role will also be responsible for the development and implementation of an effective records management and strategic framework. The Head: Legal and Auxiliary Services will form part of the Corporate Services Branch and will report to the Executive: Corporate Services.\n \nCVs should contain at least three (3) references. No hand delivered applications will be accepted.\n \nClosing date 08 July 2024. If you are not contacted by 31 August 2024, please consider your application as unsuccessful.\n \nKindly click on the links below for more information\nPnet Link:\nhttps://www.pnet.co.za/offers/offerPreview.cfm?id=3837983&click=no&rs=1&status=ONLINE&previewid=a3ef441dbcd5b64f68ff390a6a55e995\nAdvertisement on LinkedIn:\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7211377479133892608\n \n \n \n ",
                    " \n \n \n \nPAYROLL OFFICER\nPermanent\n \nThis position calls for an energetic and dynamic person to assist in administering all payroll functions, while ensuring a high degree of confidentiality as well as accuracy, integrity and compliance. The successful candidate will be a member of the Finance Branch and will report to the Financial Manager.\n \nCVs should contain at least three (3) references. No hand delivered applications will be accepted.\n \nClosing date 08 July 2024. If you are not contacted by 31 August 2024, please consider your application as unsuccessful.\n \nKindly click on the links below for more information\nPnet Link:\nhttps://www.pnet.co.za/offers/offerPreview.cfm?id=3838080&click=no&rs=1&status=ONLINE&previewid=744273aabd53ed9a57b9124da4609fa4\nLinkedIn Link:\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7211377936044609536\n \n \n \n \n ",
                    "IT ADMINISTRATOR - PERMANENT\n \nThe Water Research Commission is constantly looking for more efficient and effective ways of using technology to improve organisational Support and to meet the IT needs of all staff members. If you are a skilled, motivated, and dedicated IT Administrator who will be able to maintain the company's ICT network, servers and security systems which includes specific projects to ensure business continuity, then this opportunity is for you.\n \nThe position of an IT Administrator will provide you with a view of the IT technical operations and allow you to explore all aspects of application architecture, process automation, solution design, scaling, testing, and reporting. You will also have the exciting opportunity to work with great technologies alongside a high performing and creative team providing technical support to end-users, attending to IT queries. The IT Administrator will form part of the CEO's office Team and will report to the IT Infrastructure Manager.\n \nCVs should contain at least three (3) references. No hand delivered applications will be accepted.\n \nClosing date 08 July 2024. \n \nIf you are not contacted by 31 August 2024, please consider your application as unsuccessful.\n \nPnet Link:\nhttps://www.pnet.co.za/offers/offerPreview.cfm?id=3838042&click=no&rs=1&status=ONLINE&previewid=dd523e5d34def68fec960aef028056ca\nLinkedIn Link:\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7211378268615147521",
                    "CHIEF INFORMATION OFFICER\nFixed Term: 5 Year Contract\n \nThe position of a Chief Information Officer will be responsible for the development and implementation of the ICT strategy and initiatives, ICT risk management and overall management and control of ICT operations and systems that are integral to research and innovation as well as implement cost-effective and critical business systems that are reliable, secured and aligned to appropriate best practices. This includes development and implementation of a strategic ICT governance framework, policies and standards for Information Communications and Technology (ICT) that are aligned to the organisational strategy, ensuring services, and overall management and control of ICT operations. Furthermore, the incumbent will be responsible for providing vision and leadership for developing and implementing information system initiatives that are aligned to the WRC strategy, transforming the ICT service to deliver a seamless high- quality service across the organisation and ensuring the adherence to all governance frameworks for digital technology and information required to ensure that digital technology enables the WRC to achieve its core purpose and mandate, reduce risk and enable the business to carry out their duties.\n \nApplicants must be in possession of an NQF Level 7 Qualification in Information System/Information Technology/Computer Science or related field. A Post graduate qualification in Information System/Information Technology/Computer Science/business management or related field will be an added advantage. A minimum of or in a similar position with at least 5 years of which should be in management position(s). Experience in Public or water sector at a senior management level will be an added advantage. plan and individuals with a disability and designated groups are encouraged to apply.\n \nApplications must be submitted via the email address to ciowrc@mjvrecruitment.co.za, and CVs should contain at least three (3) references. \nNo hand delivered applications will be accepted. \n \nFor enquiries, please call Ms. Mashudu Ndou on 011 410 9477. \n \nThe closing date is 02 July 2024"
