                    " \nKZN GROWTH FUND\n ",
                    " \nPRINCIPAL: DEBT OFFICER \nSALARY: MARKET RELATED \n \nKZN Growth Fund is a private equity and private debt Fund based in Durban reporting to the KwaZulu-Natal Department of Economic Development, Tourism and Environmental Affairs (EDTEA). The Fund seeks to appoint an experienced and suitably qualified Principal: Debt Officer. \n\nThe ideal candidate will be responsible for the origination, execution and closing of prospective mid-market debt investments to achieve KZN Growth Fund\u2019 developmental targets and investment returns. In addition, he/she must be able to effectively lead and direct junior members of the investment team and also assist management in formulating, planning, developing and implementing the Fund\u2019s investment strategy. \n \nThe ideal individual will be responsible for: \nSupport the Chief Investment Officer (CIO) in crafting and executing the Fund\u2019s business and action plan. \nLead the identification, selection, origination and execution of debt and quasi-debt transactions, including screening of prospective investments, assessing project risks and advising on appropriate risk mitigation actions. \nDevelop creative and appropriate financial structures for complex transactions, assessing and structuring transactions to improve the potential for co-financing and catalyzing of additional sources of capital. \nCoordinate with experts/specialists in areas like environmental, social and governance, technical, legal, and risk functions as it relates to project structuring and closing of deals. \nLead and coordinate the preparation and presentation of investment reports to the various decision-making committees of the Fund. \nLead industry and market research to guide the business origination and execution effort, aligned with the Fund\u2019s investment criteria and mandate. \nMaintain knowledge of the debt portfolio, including leading preparation of lessons learned from projects and disseminating information to investment teams. \nPromoting KZN Growth Fund through developing key relationships in the private sector and development communities. \nProvide leadership, coaching, mentoring and support to junior team members. \nDraft and maintain good investment policies and procedures. \n \nThe following minimum requirements must be met in order to be considered for this position: \nB Com Honours, Post Graduate Diploma, CFA, MBA or similar equivalent qualification \nMinimum of 10 years\u2019 experience in lending environment, development finance, management consulting, corporate finance or similar field \nStrong credit skills, due diligence, financial modelling & structuring capabilities \nUnderstanding of corporate finance principles \n \n \nKZN GROWTH FUND TRUST EMBRACES THE PRINCIPLES OF THE EMPLOYMENT EQUITY ACT. \n \nDesignated group candidates are strongly encouraged to apply. \n \nCorrespondence will be limited to short-listed candidates. Late applications will not be considered. Email users are requested to set the delivery option on both \u201creturn receipt\u201d and \u201cconfirm delivery\u201d. If you have not been contacted within 30 days of the closing date of the advertisement, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful. \n \nInterested applicants should forward a detailed CV, certified copies of qualifications and ID document to: \nrecruitment1@kzngf.co.za\n \nCLOSING DATE: 27 JUNE 2024\n \n \n \n \n ",
                    " \n \n \n \nINVESTMENT OFFICER X2 \nSALARY: MARKET RELATED \n \nKZN Growth Fund is a private equity and private debt Fund based in Durban reporting to the KwaZulu Natal Department of Economic Development, Tourism and Environmental Affairs (EDTEA). The Fund seeks to appoint an experienced and suitably qualified Investment Officer. \nReporting to the Chief Investment Officer, the successful candidate will be responsible for sourcing and screening investment opportunities, executing and closing transactions and actively managing portfolio investments. The role requires an individual that is driven by their commitment to contribute to private sector development, broad-based black economic empowerment and improving the lives of people in KwaZulu Natal by executing innovative, developmental, and profitable investments for the KZN Growth Fund. \n \nKey performance areas: \nSolicit appropriate investment opportunities and conduct initial screening of projects in terms of the Fund\u2019s investment policies. \nUndertake and present full appraisals of debt and equity transactions to the Fund\u2019s various decision-making Committees. \nEnsure deal closure by taking responsibility for optimal financial, institutional and legal structuring. \nCoordinate with the legal team for the conclusion of transaction agreements. \nProvide innovative and flexible financial structures for complex transactions. \nIdentify opportunities to initiate viable projects, project origination through the facilitation of project preparation, scoping, feasibility studies, and business plans with the intention of closing investment deals. \nPerform equity valuations of investee companies. \nIdentifying the exit opportunity and timing, and assisting in the exit from equity portfolio investments. \nSupport the Chief Investment Officer and Chief Executive Officer in drafting and presentation of reports, evaluations, plans, etc. related to the business of the KZN Growth Fund. \nDevelop and maintain relationships with a broad spectrum of project finance funders and private equity institutions, which should include local and international institutions, commercial banks, development finance institutions, ECAs and multi-lateral agencies. \nUndertake continuous research and provide recommendations on significant developments, emerging opportunities and challenges in the areas of responsibility. \n \nThe following minimum requirements must be met to be considered for this position: \nAn Honours Degree in Finance/Banking/Economics/Engineering and related fields \nA post-graduate qualification such as CA, CFA or MBA would be a strong advantage \nAt least 5 years\u2019 experience in project finance and private equity with a proven track record in project origination, appraisal and deal closure or Structured Finance transactions in a financial institution \nProven experience in Financial Modelling, Financial Analysis, Due Diligence Investigations, financial structuring, valuation and risk identification and mitigation \nUnderstanding of project and commercial agreements such as off take agreements, EPC/M contracts, operations and maintenance agreements, shareholder agreements, CTA, inter-creditor and facility agreements \n \n \nKZN GROWTH FUND TRUST EMBRACES THE PRINCIPLES OF THE EMPLOYMENT EQUITY ACT. \n \nDesignated group candidates are strongly encouraged to apply. \n \nCorrespondence will be limited to short-listed candidates. Late applications will not be considered. Email users are requested to set the delivery option on both \u201creturn receipt\u201d and \u201cconfirm delivery\u201d. If you have not been contacted within 30 days of the closing date of the advertisement, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful. \n \nInterested applicants should forward a detailed CV, certified copies of qualifications and ID document to: \nrecruitment1@kzngf.co.za\n \nCLOSING DATE: 27 JUNE 2024\n \n \n \n ",
                    " \n \n \n \nMANAGEMENT ACCOUNTANT \nSALARY: MARKET RELATED\n \nKZN Growth Fund is a private equity and private debt Fund based in Durban reporting to the KwaZulu Natal Department of Economic Development, Tourism and Environmental Affairs (EDTEA). The Fund seeks to appoint an experienced and suitably qualified Management Accountant. \nReporting to the Finance Manager, the successful candidate will be responsible for managing Budget preparation, forecasting and management. Ensure appropriate performance management and related reporting. \n \nKey Performance Areas: \nPreparation of annual budgets and reporting thereon. \nPreparation and monitoring of quarterly budgets for the corporate plan, annual performance plan from different departments. \nMonitor JIBAR rates to provide feedback to FM and CFO. \nAssist with accounting duties for KGFT subsidiary which performs Private Equity Fund activities, PI Insurance cover for KGFT Capital implementation and Maintenance.\nPrepare (monthly, quarterly and annual) forecasts including capital allocations. \nAssist internal and external auditors with required information through the various avenues in the organisation. \nConstruct data accumulation systems. \nManage the costs in line with spending strategy and provide the advice to FM and CFO on cost saving measures. \nPrepare budgeting reports (for the company and for each department) in line with Treasury Regulations and PFMA. \nAnalyze and report profit margins against budgets. \nSuper user in the fund Model system in relation to finance reports. \nPrepare (monthly, quarterly and annual) forecasts including capital allocations \nAssisting in month-end and year-end closing. \nIdentify and recommend cost-effective solutions by providing valuable insight from variance analysis. \nAssist with accounting duties for KGFT subsidiary which performs Private Equity Fund activities. \n \nThe following minimum requirements must be met in order to be considered for this position: \nB.Com and relevant Post Graduate qualification in Accounting \nSAICA / CIMA affiliation will be an added advantage \nMinimum of 5 years\u2019 experience in the management accountant and understanding of audit environment \nPrevious PFMA experience / knowledge\n \n \nKZN GROWTH FUND TRUST EMBRACES THE PRINCIPLES OF THE EMPLOYMENT EQUITY ACT. \n \nDesignated group candidates are strongly encouraged to apply. \nCorrespondence will be limited to short-listed candidates. Late applications will not be considered. Email users are requested to set the delivery option on both \u201creturn receipt\u201d and \u201cconfirm delivery\u201d. If you have not been contacted within 30 days of the closing date of the advertisement, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful. \n \nInterested applicants may forward a detailed CV, certified copies of qualifications and ID document to: \nrecruitment1@kzngf.co.za\n \nCLOSING DATE: 27 JUNE 2024\n \n \n \n \n ",
                    "LEGAL & RECOVERIES OFFICER \nSALARY: MARKET RELATED \n \nKZN Growth Fund is a private equity and private debt Fund based in Durban reporting to the KwaZulu-Natal Department of Economic Development, Tourism and Environmental Affairs (EDTEA). The Fund seeks to appoint an experienced and suitably Legal & Recoveries Officer. \nReporting to the General Legal Counsel, the successful candidate will be responsible to manage the activities focused on recoveries from defaulting clients, including liaising with external legal advisers/liquidators and business rescue practitioners Ancillary activities will include providing support to the legal and compliance function in transaction execution and post-transaction monitoring for the KZN Growth Fund. \n \nKey performance areas: \nMonitoring external information sources (e.g. credit bureau reports) for indications of potential or actual default. \nDrafting legal documentation relating to recoveries. \nFormulating appropriate recovery strategies to optimize recoveries relative to time and cost. \nEngaging with executives and post investment officers on recovery activities & strategies. \nInitiating, considering and finalizing settlement proposals and negotiations. \nInstructing panel attorneys to institute legal action against defaulting clients and management of legal process until resolution. \nInstructing third party service providers (e.g. auctioneers) and monitor progress. \nRigorous management of costs of external legal advisers, counsel and third party service providers. \nMaintaining effective and professional working relationships with attorneys, insolvency practitioners, business rescue practitioners and auctioneers. \nMonitoring progress on matters underway in the courts, under business rescue and liquidation. \nProvide legal advice and services to the organization in corporate and commercial matters, relating to recovery. \nAttend internal and external committee meetings to present any report on an ad hoc basis. \nOn request attend to due diligence investigations, security assessments and reporting on projects at application phase. \nA thorough understanding of the legal and compliance functions for loan transaction and documentation execution and to assist in this regard when required. \nUndertake continuous research and provide recommendations on significant developments, emerging opportunities and challenges in the areas of responsibility. \nRegular reporting, monthly quarterly and annually. \n \nThe following minimum requirements must be met to be considered for this position: \nLLB Degree with commercial qualification \nAdmitted Attorney with at least 3 years post article experience \nAt least 3 years\u2019 experience in a litigation/recoveries role within a financial institution with a focus on debt recovery from businesses/corporates [not individuals] \nAt least 3 - 8 years job related corporate and commercial law and banking and finance principles \nUnderstanding of project and commercial agreements such as off take agreements, EPC/M contracts, operations and maintenance agreements, shareholder agreements, CTA, inter-creditor and facility \nAbility to communicate at all levels, both internally and externally \n \n \n \nKZN GROWTH FUND TRUST EMBRACES THE PRINCIPLES OF THE EMPLOYMENT EQUITY ACT. \n \nDesignated group candidates are strongly encouraged to apply. \n \nCorrespondence will be limited to short-listed candidates. Late applications will not be considered. Email users are requested to set the delivery option on both \u201creturn receipt\u201d and \u201cconfirm delivery\u201d. If you have not been contacted within 30 days of the closing date of the advertisement, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful. \n \nInterested applicants should forward a detailed CV, certified copies of qualifications and ID document to: \nrecruitment1@kzngf.co.za\n \nCLOSING DATE: 27 JUNE 2024.",
                    "CREDIT AND INVESTMENT MONITORING OFFICER \nSALARY: MARKET RELATED \n \nKZN Growth Fund is a private equity and private debt Fund based in Durban reporting to the KwaZulu-Natal Department of KZN Economic Development, Tourism and Environmental Affairs (EDTEA). The Fund seeks to appoint an experienced and suitably qualified Credit and Investment Monitoring Officer. \nThe appointee will be required to conduct credit assessment and risk appraisals of the organisations investments, perform pre and post investment activities, with respect to credit management functions, in adherence with the credit and equity policies of the organisation. \n \nThe ideal individual will be allocated the following responsibilities: \nCredit risk and post investment monitoring of the organization\u2019s investments. \nPhysical monitoring of project progress from financial close, in line with terms of the investment agreements, including portfolio performance and analysis, valuations of investee companies and project management. \nConducting regular client visits. \nCompile monthly/quarterly/bi-annual and annual investment review reports and plans for various committees. \nDevelopment and implementation of a turnaround plan or strategy for the investee company. \nImpairment management. \nCredit and post investment policy reviews. \nOther credit risk related ad hoc activities. \n \nThe following minimum requirements must be met in order to be considered for this position: \nB Com Honours (with majors in Accounting or equivalent NQF8) \nMinimum of 5 years\u2019 experience in project finance / private equity or in a similar finance service environment. \nStrong financial analysis \nPost-investment risk management. \n \n \n \nKZN GROWTH FUND TRUST EMBRACES THE PRINCIPLES OF THE EMPLOYMENT EQUITY ACT. \n \nDesignated group candidates are strongly encouraged to apply. \n \nCorrespondence will be limited to short-listed candidates. Late applications will not be considered. Email users are requested to set the delivery option on both \u201creturn receipt\u201d and \u201cconfirm delivery\u201d. If you have not been contacted within 30 days of the closing date of the advertisement, please accept that your application has been unsuccessful. \n \nInterested applicants should forward a detailed CV, certified copies of qualifications and ID document to: \nrecruitment1@kzngf.co.za\nCLOSING DATE: 27 June 2024\n \n \nKZN Growth Fund Trust \nT+27 31 372 3720 \nF+27 31 306 2547 \nkzngrowthfund.co.za\n \nPhysical\n28th Floor Delta Towers \n303 Dr. Pixley Kaseme (West) Street \nDurban 4001 \n \nPostal\nP.O. Box 1817 \nDurban 4001 \nSouth Africa \n \nBoard of Trustees: Dr. RC. Lubisi (Chairperson) / Ms. BS. Mzobe / Ms. B. Dlamini / Ms. S. Mamvura / Mr. S. Thobela / Mr. T. Hlongwa / Ms. B. Ikaneng (Acting CEO) Ex officio. Mr. M. Dlamini (Acting Chief Financial Officer) / Ms. TP. Nxumalo (Company Secretary) Registration No. IT1437/2007(PMB)"
