                    " \nAUTOMOTIVE INDUSTRY DEVELOPMENT CENTRE (AIDC)\n ",
                    "BUSINESS INCUBATEE\n(5-year Automotive Incubation Programme) \n\u2022 Pretoria\n \n\u2022 Automotive Industry Development Centre's (AIDC) Supplier Incubation Programme \u2022 The Supplier Park Development Company (SOC) Ltd, trading as ADC, is a government-owned, public entity company established to provide support to the SA Automotive \u2022 Industry in its drive for global competitiveness. It is a dynamic company that offers exciting career opportunities. \u2022 The ADC currently has two operational business incubators in the automotive industry based in Gauteng. The ADC aims to recruit Incubatees that will be based at one of the Original Equipment Manufacturers Incubation facilities located in Pretoria. \u2022 In support of this, the AIDC are embarking on a recruitment drive for incumbents who will become Incubatees within the Incubation Programme whereby they would spend an average of five years on the Programme (subject to agreed performance targets). \u2022 During this period, the Incubatees will be trained and mentored by the ADC as well as a technical partner to become proficient in operating a manufacturing business within the automotive industry. \u2022 The Incubates will 'graduate' from the programme with the required skills and a registered company with a proven delivery track record, at a minimum. \u2022 Purpose of position: Inclusion into ADC's Incubation Development Programme to develop the successful candidate to become a fully competent entrepreneur. Preference will be given to previously disadvantaged candidates. \n\n \nQualifications and experience: \u2022 Grade 12; National Diploma in Engineering or higher \u2022 A minimum of 5 years' technical/production experience within the automotive/manufacturing industry \u2022 A Supervisory and/or Entrepreneurial Management qualification will be an advantage \u2022 5 years' management experience within the automotive industry will be an advantage \u2022 Experience in supplying to an OEM will be an advantage \u2022 Experience in operational, financial, marketing, OMS, logistics, business development and HR will be an advantage \u2022 Preference will be given to Gauteng-based candidates.\n \nThe incumbent should demonstrate entrepreneurial attributes such as: \u2022 Innovative thinking \u2022 Analytical skills \u2022 Leadership skills \u2022 Resilience \u2022 Creativity \u2022 Tenacity \u2022 Strong work ethic \u2022 Numeracy sigh \u2022 Tolerance \u2022 Self-confidence \u2022 Ethical \u2022 Project management \u2022 Effective communication (verbal, written) \u2022 Risk Management.",
                    "If you are interested in this position and have the relevant experience, please forward your CV with full personal details, education, work history and contactable references to e-mail: AdminHRIC@aidc.co.za\n \nThe closing date for applications is 28 June 2024.\n \nNote: \u2022 Correspondence and communication will only be conducted with short-listed candidates \n\u2022 Short-listed candidates will be subjected to appropriate psychometric bet and a battery of assessments as part of the selection process \n\u2022 Background checks will be conducted with employment references, qualifications and criminal record \n\u2022 Comprehensive interview and assessment processes will be conducted on shod-listed candidates \n\u2022 There will be a Pre-Incubation process to ensure the most appropriate candidates are selected for the programme."
